{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/blog/how-to-create-most-captivating-ads-holidays-2018/","result":{"data":{"post":{"id":"cG9zdDoyODAw","excerpt":"<p>In our last blog, we spoke about the benefits of starting your holiday native advertising strategy early. Now, we’re showing you how to create the most visually captivating ads that attract attention and clicks. Beautiful, effective ads are just a few simple steps away. Here are some guidelines for creating your own: 1. Choose lifestyle [&hellip;]</p>\n","content":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In our last blog, we spoke about the benefits of <a href=\"/2018/09/06/timeline-for-holiday-advertising-campaigns-2018/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">starting your holiday native advertising strategy early</a>. Now, we’re showing you how to create the most visually captivating ads that attract attention and clicks. B</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">eautiful, effective ads are just a few simple steps away. Here are some guidelines for creating your own:</span></p>\n<h4><b>1. Choose lifestyle images.</b></h4>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Native ads are successful not just because of their position on a page, but also because of their ability to blend with the content on those pages. For native ads, we’ve found that lifestyle images outperform infographics and standalone product images. We always recommend using your product in context, in a way that will integrate well with other content on a publisher’s site.</span></p>\n<table border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"https://triplelift.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Pets-CBS-image.jpg\"><span class=\"wp-image-2875 aligncenter inline-gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%;width:300px\" data-reactroot=\"\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:200%\"></span><img aria-hidden